# Language: Medora-S (French-only product UI)

- **Discussion & implementation** (with AI, in code comments, internal docs): may be **English**.
- **User-facing product text** in Medora-S: **French only**. No bilingual UI—do not mix French and English on the same screen for end users.
- **Internal code identifiers** (filenames, variables, routes, DB fields): may stay **English**.

## Must be French (visible to users)

- Navigation, page titles, buttons, labels, placeholders
- Table headers, empty states, loading text, helper text
- Validation, success, and error messages shown in the UI
- Dashboard copy; map raw API enums to French labels when displayed

## May stay English

- Code, APIs, Prisma, logs, commit messages (optional)

## Examples

- UI: “Chargement…”, “Annuler”, “Aucun résultat”—not “Loading…”, “Cancel”, “No results.”
